atter from satellite galaxies, lowering their\naccelerations below the $a_{\\rm min}\\sim 10^{-11} m/s^2$ minimum expected for\nisolated dwarfs. In many cases, the resulting velocity dispersions are\ninconsistent with the predictions from Modified Newtonian Dynamics, a result\nthat poses a possibly insurmountable challenge to that scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Jul 2017 20:32:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Mar 2018 16:34:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-03-16"}
